            <div>
                <entry xml:id="L6730f7b0a19b42ba9dceae9bf36994e7" n="12356">
                    <form>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">አክሶስያ</foreign>
                    </form>
                    <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>ʾaksosyā</quote>
                        </cit> <gramGrp>
                            <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos>
                        </gramGrp> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>authority</quote>
                        </cit>’, here it is rendered as ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>divinity</quote>
                        </cit>’ <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሄጴሙሰ፡ እምነ፡ አክሶስየ። ዘኢሰሐጦ፡ ባዕድ፡ ጕሕልያ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>Lamp from the divinity whom the alien cheater did not swindle!</quote>
                        </cit>’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 134 (430) l. 19-20 (ed.); 135 (431) l. 21-22 (tr.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl> (‘<cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>Akǝsosǝya</quote>
                        </cit> is a loanword from Greek <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἐξουσία</foreign> “authority”. There is a passage ascribed to Cyril of Alexandria which says <foreign xml:lang="gez">አክሶስያ፡ ዘይደሉ፡ ለመለኮት፡ (ቄር፡ ስምዓት)።</foreign> “authority that belongs to the divinity”, cf. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:KidaneWaldGeezGramDict"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 220</citedRange>
                        </bibl>.’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 135 (431) n. 286</citedRange>
                        </bibl>) <sense n="L" xml:id="TL">
                            <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                                <quote>ʾaksosyā</quote>
                            </cit> አክሶስያ (K*) <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                                <quote>power</quote>
                            </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                                <quote>authority</quote>
                            </cit>; from Gk. <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                                <quote>eksousia</quote>
                            </cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                                <quote>power</quote>
                            </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                                <quote>authority</quote>
                            </cit>. <bibl>
                                <ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/>
                                <citedRange unit="page"> 16b</citedRange>
                            </bibl> </sense> <nd/> </sense>
                    
                </entry>
